# Plain Codex Mode

Use normal Codex behavior for this session.
Do not apply the lecture-note automation workflow from AGENTS.md.

## Encoding and File Reading
- Always read text-based files with explicit UTF-8 decoding.
- Do not rely on Windows/PowerShell default encoding or terminal code page.
- Preferred PowerShell read command: `Get-Content -Raw -Encoding UTF8 "path/to/file"`.
- Preferred PowerShell search command: `Select-String -Encoding UTF8 -Path "path/to/file" -Pattern "..."`.
- Preferred Python read pattern: `Path(path).read_text(encoding="utf-8")` or `open(path, encoding="utf-8")`.
- If Korean text appears garbled, re-read the file explicitly as UTF-8 before editing or reporting an issue.
- If UTF-8 decoding still fails, report an encoding issue instead of guessing or silently rewriting the file.
- Binary files such as PDFs and images must be handled with appropriate parsers/renderers, not plain-text reads.

## Rules
- Follow only the user's current prompt.
- Do not create or update PLAN files unless explicitly requested.
- Do not process inbox/ or input_manifest.json unless explicitly requested.
- Inspect relevant files before editing.
- Make minimal, targeted changes.
- Report changed files and checks run.
